<h1 align="center">
Debian GNU/NetBSD
</h1>

<p>
Debian GNU/NetBSD is a port of the Debian Operating System to the NetBSD kernel. It
is currently in an early stage of development and cannot currently be installed from
scratch. Instead, a tarball of the current environment is available and can
be extracted into a directory on a NetBSD system.
</p>

<p>
<a href="http://www.srcf.ucam.org/~mjg59/debian-netbsd/debian-netbsd.tar.gz">\
Download the current version of the Debian GNU/NetBSD system</a>
(last updated 14 January 2002)
</p>

<p>
<a href="why">Why Debian GNU/NetBSD?</a>
</p>

<h2>
Usage instructions
</h2>

<ul>
<li>Download the file</li>
<li>Extract it somewhere. <b>WARNING</b> - do not extract this in / - you will render your system unbootable</li>
<li>As root, chroot /debian /bin/bash (replace /debian with wherever you've extracted the tarball)</li>
<li>Play. Enjoy. Fix stuff.</li>
</ul>

